---
import TutorialLayout from '../../../layouts/TutorialLayout.astro';
import TutorialPlayground from '../../../components/TutorialPlayground.astro';
---

<TutorialLayout 
  title="Math Operations" 
  description="Learn arithmetic operations in Python"
  currentPage={3}
  totalPages={10}
  prevLink="/en/materi/02-variables"
  nextLink="/en/materi/04-strings"
>
  <div slot="content">
    <h1>Math Operations</h1>
    
    <p>Python can perform mathematical calculations using arithmetic operators. Let's explore the basic math operations.</p>
    
    <h2>Arithmetic Operators</h2>
    
    <table class="w-full border-collapse border border-border">
      <thead>
        <tr class="bg-muted">
          <th class="border border-border p-2 text-left">Operator</th>
          <th class="border border-border p-2 text-left">Operation</th>
          <th class="border border-border p-2 text-left">Example</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>+</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Addition</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>5 + 3 = 8</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>-</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Subtraction</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>5 - 3 = 2</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>*</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Multiplication</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>5 * 3 = 15</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>/</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Division</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>6 / 3 = 2.0</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>**</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Exponentiation</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>2 ** 3 = 8</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>//</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Floor Division</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>7 // 3 = 2</code></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>%</code></td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2">Modulus (Remainder)</td>
          <td class="border border-border p-2"><code>7 % 3 = 1</code></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    
    <h2>Order of Operations</h2>
    
    <p>Python follows the standard mathematical order of operations (PEMDAS):</p>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>P</strong>arentheses</li>
      <li><strong>E</strong>xponents</li>
      <li><strong>M</strong>ultiplication and <strong>D</strong>ivision (left to right)</li>
      <li><strong>A</strong>ddition and <strong>S</strong>ubtraction (left to right)</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h2>Using Variables in Math</h2>
    
    <p>You can use variables in mathematical expressions and store the results in new variables.</p>
    
    <h2>Try it yourself</h2>
    
    <p>Experiment with different mathematical operations. Try:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Changing the values of <code>a</code> and <code>b</code></li>
      <li>Adding parentheses to change the order of operations</li>
      <li>Creating your own calculations</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <div slot="playground">
    <TutorialPlayground 
      code={`# Basic arithmetic operations
a = 10
b = 3

print(f"a = {a}, b = {b}")
print()

print(f"Addition: {a} + {b} = {a + b}")
print(f"Subtraction: {a} - {b} = {a - b}")
print(f"Multiplication: {a} * {b} = {a * b}")
print(f"Division: {a} / {b} = {a / b}")
print(f"Exponentiation: {a} ** {b} = {a ** b}")
print(f"Floor Division: {a} // {b} = {a // b}")
print(f"Modulus: {a} % {b} = {a % b}")

print()
print("Order of operations:")
result1 = 2 + 3 * 4
result2 = (2 + 3) * 4
print(f"2 + 3 * 4 = {result1}")
print(f"(2 + 3) * 4 = {result2}")

# Try your own calculations below:
x = 15
y = 4
# Add your code here`}
    />
  </div>
</TutorialLayout>